my best friend from grade school killed herself on saturday

<lj-cut text="Tuesday, January 6th, 2004"> - D'ALESSANDRO, ERICA - Erica D'Alessandro of Fort Lee, NJ died Saturday, January 3, 2004. She was 18 years old. Erica was born March 8, 1985 in Bronxville, NY, daughter of John and Andrea (Cmar) D'Alessandro. She had lived in Tuckahoe before moving to Fort Lee and had graduated from The Ursuline School in New Rochelle, NY. Erica was the manager of Curves for Women at the Fort Lee location. Besides her parents, Erica is survived by her sister Alaina D'Alessandro. A Mass of Christian Burial will be celebrated on Thursday, January 8, 2004, 10 am at Our Lady of the Lake Church, Carmel, NY. Interment will follow in St. Lawrence O'Toole Cemetery, Brewster, NY. The wake will begin on Wednesday the 7th from 2-4 and 7-9 pm at Beecher Funeral Home. Contributions in her memory may be made to: Van Ost Institute, 150 East Palisades Ave., Englewood, NJ 07631. BEECHER FUNERAL HOME 1 Putnam Ave., Brewster 845-279-3615 www.beecherfuneralhome.com

and we'll stay like this all gold and green. 
Light collects and projects your heart on a  movie screen
and if you close your eyes we will always be the way we were that night you crawled inside of me
and slept in my blood the way you sleep now.
the quietest hush has consumed this house
and when the doctors have gone and you sweat through the bed
with the pictures and pills piled around your head,
just rest now.

at OLIVE'S. 
yeah!
one time this guy who was really italian and equally as drunk said this:

"hey"

then he says  "wanna hang out?"

i want alot. but it's not too much. 
i want to forget.
i want to remember.
i want to stop


the truth is you can be orphaned again and again and again.
the truth is you will be.
